You'll notice with your Facebook news feed when it first loads you'll

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:05.540
see some empty stories.

00:01:05.540 --> 00:01:07.710
That's Facebook following the technique you see right here.

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:10.800
And the same thing is true for Google searches.

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:14.340
When you search for something, you'll see the header come back before the search

00:01:14.340 --> 00:01:17.430
results start filling in, because this is a really great trick for

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:19.740
getting content on the screen as fast as possible.

